gomodel:SYNGO_797  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 6; LRRTM1 mediate postsynaptic differenziation\nLiteral:\n\"The antibody-coated beads induced robust clustering of YFP-LRRTMs at nonsynaptic sites (sites lacking VGLUT1 or VGAT) on the dendrites. Such artificial clustering of YFP-LRRTMs resulted in coclustering of the glutamatergic postsynaptic proteins NMDA receptor essential subunit NR1 (Figures 6A and 6B),\"\n\n8/6/2017 Pim\n- Postsynaptic density is inferred form aggregation of both NR1 and PSD95 proteins, markers of synaptic densities.. Experimental description: Rat YFP-LRRTM1 overexpression in rat hippocampal neurons and COS cells was used\n\nLiteral\n\"Cloning full-length LRRTMs\nFull length cDNAs for LRRTMs were made using RT-PCR from p11 rat brain total RNA.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_797" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

